      "path": "vizumap-example/MapStimulus.tsx",
      "parameters": {
        "description": {
          "text": "The map below shows estimated family poverty data in the USA in 2015. Each region on the map has a colour that shows the estimated poverty level, and how uncertain that estimation is. The diamond legend on the right shows the values for the colours, with the left side (pov_rate) showing the poverty rate, and the right side (pov_error) showing how uncertain the poverty rate data is. The colours mix together to show both.",
